Issues.Body:
**What version of Tailwind CSS are you using?**

"tailwindcss": "^4.0.0-beta.7",

**What build tool (or framework if it abstracts the build tool) are you using?**

Next.js 15

**What version of Node.js are you using?**

v22

**What browser are you using?**

N/A

**What operating system are you using?**

Windows

**Describe your issue**

Overriding the default colors is not possible, here is example theme config:

This leads to the color config being ignored.

@theme {
  --color-neutral-50: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-50));
  --color-neutral-100: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-100));
  --color-neutral-200: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-200));
  --color-neutral-300: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-300));
  --color-neutral-400: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-400));
  --color-neutral-500: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-500));
  --color-neutral-600: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-600));
  --color-neutral-700: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-700));
  --color-neutral-800: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-800));
  --color-neutral-900: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-900));
  --color-neutral-950: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-950));
  }
  
  The only way i can make it work is by renaming it to v2neutral:
  
  @theme {
  --color-v2neutral-50: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-50));
  --color-v2neutral-100: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-100));
  --color-v2neutral-200: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-200));
  --color-v2neutral-300: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-300));
  --color-v2neutral-400: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-400));
  --color-v2neutral-500: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-500));
  --color-v2neutral-600: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-600));
  --color-v2neutral-700: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-700));
  --color-v2neutral-800: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-800));
  --color-v2neutral-900: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-900));
  --color-v2neutral-950: oklch(var(--my-custom-neutral-950));
    }

when working with typescript face correct typing issue

when using like this
```js
addVariant(`selector`, (({ modifySelectors, separator, }) => {
    modifySelectors(({ className }) => {
        return `.${e(`selector${separator}${className}`)}[type="${type}"]`;
    });
}));
```
